t on another online game. DAOC seems to be the biggest newcomer so I have some questions if that is where I go.<br>
 <br>
#1 I have heard the combat/pulling system is poor. For example if you have 2 people in your group you can only get two mobs, making the margin for error huge. I dislike this(how can I train people if I can only pull one mob? :P). Could anyone elaborate on the system?<br>
<br>
#2 What is rangerish in DAOC? If any former rangers play could you give me a comparison of DAOC vs EQ rangers, because that is the class I will play.<br>
<br>
#3 Experience system similar or different to EQ? <br>
<br>
#4 How is the communications system? <br>
<br>
#5 Is there an endgame? If so, how much has already been discovered?(took people a long time to kill vox/nag, wondering how difficult the challenges in DAOC are). <br>
<br>
#6 is PvP well designed? <br>
<br>
#7 Are they planning expansions ala EQ? <br>
<br>
I appreciate the input beforehand. Seems to be a good response to DAOC so if EQ doesn't get back into my system I'll give it a try. Lata...<br>
<br>
Gilg <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vendrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1191<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/10/02 3:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmmm</span><hr size=1> 1. Pulling system is called “BaF” and it stands for Bring a Friend. Meaning, the amount of mobs you pull is in direct proportion to your group size. In most cases, if you're solo you can pull just one mob from a camp where as a full group can pull up to 5-6. Nice concept, totally unrealistic.<br>
<br>
2. Closest matches are the archer classes. Hunter, Scout and Ranger I believe. Hands down the most popular classes for PvP. They’re the only classes that can solo and rack up more realm points than entire guilds combined in one evening.<br>
<br>
3. Different. If you pull a mob that has been sitting somewhere, untouched, for a long period of time you get a camp bonus(anti-camp would be more accurate), its to encourage people to move around. A second bonus that you can get is a group bonus, pull more than 1 at a time and you get that.<br>
<br>
4. Good. All the same channels as EQ with the addition of alliance chat, a channel to combine entire guilds into one channel. Sounds neat, unless you have tools whining about loot in it for 45 minutes straight… oh, in beta!<br>
<br>
5. RvR is the endgame. There are no big, loot dropping mobs that I'm aware of.<br>
<br>
6. No. One class, or type of class, owns PvP.<br>
<br>
7. Most of us are of the opinion that they pulled everyone except Stewart, the intern, off the live version of DaoC to work on the expansion. Otherwise PvP might not be so broken and it wouldn’t take them 3 months to itemize zones that have been in the game since beta 2. <p><b>Vendrix</b><br>
